# Medula Wireframes — Cursor Context

## Project
Interactive wireframes for Medula mobile app — a digital oracle chat service.
Vite + React, no TypeScript, inline styles (intentional — matches Figma design token workflow).

## Design System
- All design tokens live in `src/tokens.js` — colors, fonts, spacing, sizes.
- Change visual properties ONLY through tokens, never hardcode values in components.
- Font families: Cormorant Garamond (display), DM Sans (body).
- Dark theme only. Primary bg: #0A0910. Accent: #C0A875 (gold), #A59CD9 (lavender).

## Architecture
- `src/components/` — reusable UI primitives (Phone frame, Portal, WireLabel, Icons)
- `src/screens/` — one file per screen, each receives `showLabels` prop
- `src/App.jsx` — screen navigation, labels toggle
- Screens are self-contained, no shared state between them (wireframe mode)

## Conventions
- All text in Russian (UI is Russian-only MVP)
- WireLabel = annotation for developers, togglable via showLabels prop
- Portal component = the key visual motif (animated concentric circles)
- No external component libraries — everything is custom
- SVG icons defined in Icons.jsx

## Next Steps
- Add keyboard navigation (← →) for screen switching
- Evolve into hi-fi by replacing inline styles with CSS modules
- Add Framer Motion for production-ready animations
